Description: Cylinder seal of black steatite: perforated through the centre, bearing an incised inscription. The inscription ends with the sign of a seated figure before an offering table. Good condition.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit II (Wiesbaden, 1964), 1171; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl. 112, abb. 617.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Rev George Denis Nash
